        <ul>
            <li>Click&#160;<span class="Emphasis">General</span>. This opens the&#160;General page. In the <span class="Emphasis">Windows Auto Login IP&#160;Ranges</span> box, enter one of the following:<ul><li><span class="SetOffFirstLevel">An IP&#160;Address Range </span>For example, type: <span class="TypedEntry">10.0.0.0-10.255.255.255</span>. This permits all IP addresses within that range to log on automatically. </li><li><span class="SetOffFirstLevel">Multiple IP Address Ranges </span>If you have multiple ranges, separate each range with a comma. For example, <span class="TypedEntry">0.0.0.0-10.10.10.10<span class="YellowBackground">,</span>192.168.0.0-255.255.255.255</span>.</li></ul></li>
        </ul>
